# Shopping Sync Merge Contract

- Merge semantics must remain deterministic across client and Worker.
- Keying preference and tie-break behavior must be consistent with current item-level merge strategy.
- Sync failures must not discard local list state.

## Behavioral Invariants

- `updated_at` drives last-write preference unless tie policy says otherwise.
- Merge preserves stable row shape and required fields.
- Pull/push retries must remain bounded and observable in logs/toasts.

## Verification

- Run dual-device simulation script in read-only and write mode as needed.
- Confirm no duplicate-key explosion or oscillating row resolution.
- Validate client still renders merged list and updates cloud stamp safely.
